---
import PolicyLayout from '../components/PolicyLayout.astro';
---

<PolicyLayout
  title="Cookie Policy – Omphile Pest Solutions"
  description="Omphile Pest Solutions cookie and analytics policy, including our privacy-focused Umami analytics setup."
  heroTitle="Cookie Policy"
>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <div class="policy-section" style="padding-bottom:48px;">
    <h2 class="policy-section-title-intro">About This Policy</h2>
    <div class="policy-accent-divider"></div>
    <p class="policy-section-body-dark">This Cookie Policy explains how Omphile Pest Solutions ('we', 'us', or 'our') uses cookies and similar tracking technologies on our website. We are committed to transparency and your privacy in accordance with the Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA) of South Africa.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Section 1 -->
  <div class="policy-section" style="padding-bottom:48px;">
    <h2 class="policy-section-title-lg">1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
    <div class="policy-accent-divider"></div>
    <p class="policy-section-body-dark">Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device when you visit a website. They help websites remember information about your visit, which can make your next visit easier and the site more useful to you. Some cookies are essential for the website to function, while others are used to understand how visitors interact with the site.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Section 2 -->
  <div class="policy-section" style="padding-bottom:48px;">
    <h2 class="policy-section-title-lg">2. How We Use Analytics — Umami</h2>
    <div class="policy-accent-divider"></div>
    <p class="policy-section-body-dark">We use Umami Analytics at umami.brightsync.co.za to understand how visitors use our website. Umami is a privacy-focused, open-source analytics platform that does not require visitor tracking cookies.</p>
    <div class="policy-feature-card">
      <span class="policy-feature-card-title">Why Umami is privacy-friendly:</span>
      <span class="policy-feature-card-item">&check; Does not use cookies or store any personal information</span>
      <span class="policy-feature-card-item">&check; Does not collect IP addresses or fingerprint users</span>
      <span class="policy-feature-card-item">&check; Data is fully anonymised and cannot identify you as an individual</span>
      <span class="policy-feature-card-item">&check; No cross-site tracking or sharing with third parties</span>
      <span class="policy-feature-card-item">&check; Compliant with POPIA, GDPR, CCPA, and PECR</span>
    </div>
    <p class="policy-section-body-dark" style="color:var(--text-warm-grey);margin-top:16px;">Because Umami does not use cookies and collects no personal data, no cookie consent banner is required for analytics on our website. We still maintain this policy to be fully transparent with our visitors.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Section 3 -->
  <div class="policy-section" style="padding-bottom:48px;">
    <h2 class="policy-section-title-lg">3. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
    <div class="policy-accent-divider"></div>
    <table class="policy-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Cookie Type</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
          <th>Duration</th>
          <th>Required</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Essential</td>
          <td>Basic website functionality</td>
          <td>Session</td>
          <td>Yes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Analytics</td>
          <td>None (Umami is cookieless)</td>
          <td>N/A</td>
          <td>N/A</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Marketing</td>
          <td>None — we do not use marketing cookies</td>
          <td>N/A</td>
          <td>N/A</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- Section 4 -->
  <div class="policy-section" style="padding-bottom:48px;">
    <h2 class="policy-section-title-lg">4. Managing Cookies</h2>
    <div class="policy-accent-divider"></div>
    <p class="policy-section-body-dark">Since Umami Analytics does not use cookies, there are no analytics cookies to manage or opt out of. Essential cookies required for the website to function cannot be disabled through browser settings without affecting website functionality.

Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through browser settings. Please refer to your browser's help documentation to learn how to manage cookies:</p>
    <div class="policy-browser-list">
      <span class="policy-browser-list-item">&bull; Google Chrome: Settings &rarr; Privacy and Security &rarr; Cookies</span>
      <span class="policy-browser-list-item">&bull; Mozilla Firefox: Options &rarr; Privacy & Security &rarr; Cookies and Site Data</span>
      <span class="policy-browser-list-item">&bull; Safari: Preferences &rarr; Privacy &rarr; Cookies and website data</span>
      <span class="policy-browser-list-item">&bull; Microsoft Edge: Settings &rarr; Cookies and site permissions</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Section 5 -->
  <div class="policy-section" style="padding-bottom:48px;">
    <h2 class="policy-section-title-lg">5. Your Rights Under POPIA</h2>
    <div class="policy-accent-divider"></div>
    <p class="policy-section-body-dark">Under the Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA) No. 4 of 2013, you have the right to:

&bull; Know what personal information we hold about you
&bull; Request correction of inaccurate personal information
&bull; Request deletion of your personal information
&bull; Object to the processing of your personal information
&bull; Lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator of South Africa

Since Umami does not collect or store personal information about visitors, exercising these rights in relation to analytics is not applicable. For any other personal data we may hold (such as enquiry or booking information), contact us directly.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Section 6 -->
  <div class="policy-section" style="padding-bottom:48px;">
    <h2 class="policy-section-title-lg">6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <div class="policy-accent-divider"></div>
    <p class="policy-section-body-dark">We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in technology, legislation, or our data practices. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Section 7 -->
  <div class="policy-section" style="padding-bottom:0;">
    <h2 class="policy-section-title-lg">7. Contact Us</h2>
    <div class="policy-accent-divider"></div>
    <p class="policy-section-body-dark">If you have any questions about this Cookie Policy or how we handle data, please contact our Information Officer:</p>
    <div class="policy-contact-card">
      <span class="policy-contact-card-name">Omphile Pest Solutions</span>
      <span class="policy-contact-card-text">Information Officer: pestsolutions@omphilebotshelo.co.za</span>
      <span class="policy-contact-card-text">Phone: +27 76 280 5241</span>
      <span class="policy-contact-card-text">Address: Mafikeng, North West, South Africa</span>
    </div>
    <div class="policy-regulator-box">
      <span class="policy-regulator-title">Information Regulator of South Africa</span>
      <span class="policy-regulator-text">If you believe we have not handled your personal information appropriately, you may lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator at: inforeg.org.za</span>
    </div>
  </div>

</PolicyLayout>
